1.11 Part j
Create a function called evaluate.row(...) that takes one argument and returns “low” when the argument is less than 4, “mid” when the argument is between 4 and 7 (inclusive), and “high” when the arguement is 8 or larger. Then, use sapply(...) to apply it to column x1.
Solution
I made the function here. It uses if, else if, else to evaluate the three cases the integer could fall into. Then i use sapply to apply the function to the entire column x1 in the df. It acts like a nice for loop to keep applying the function to each number in the vector column.



Code
eval.row = function(num){
  if(num&lt;4){
    return("low")
  } else if(num&gt;=8){
    return("high")
  }else{
    return("mid")
  }
}
